Your GitHub repo now has 3 files: `README.md`, `server.js`, `package.json`. ✅

---

### Part 2 — Deploy on Railway (2 min)

**1.** Go to [railway.app/new](https://railway.app/new) → click **"Deploy from GitHub repo"**

**2.** Authorize Railway to access GitHub → select `hunar-n8n-bridge` repo

**3.** Railway auto-detects Node.js and starts deploying. Wait ~30 seconds.

**4.** Once deployed, click your project → go to **"Variables"** tab → click **"New Variable"** → add:

| Variable name | Value |
|---|---|
| `N8N_WEBHOOK_URL` | `https://your-instance.app.n8n.cloud/webhook/your-path` |

Railway restarts automatically after you save the variable.

**5.** Click **"Settings"** tab → scroll to **"Domains"** → click **"Generate Domain"**

You'll get a URL like:
```
https://hunar-n8n-bridge-production.up.railway.app
```

---

